      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:1:1:33",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " لَيْسَ بَيْنَ الْإِيمَانِ وَ الْكُفْرِ إِلَّا قِلَّةُ الْعَقْلِ قِيلَ وَ كَيْفَ ذَاكَ يَا ابْنَ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ قَالَ إِنَّ الْعَبْدَ يَرْفَعُ رَغْبَتَهُ إِلَى مَخْلُوقٍ فَلَوْ أَخْلَصَ نِيَّتَهُ لِلَّهِ لَأَتَاهُ الَّذِي يُرِيدُ فِي أَسْرَعَ مِنْ ذَلِكَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Muhammad, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from his father, from one of our companions, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘There isn’t anything between the <span class=\"iTxt\">Eman</span> and the disbelief (<span class=\"iTxt\">Kufr</span>) except for the scarcity of the intellect’. It was said, ‘And how is that so, O son<sup>asws</sup> of Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup>! The servant raises his desire to the creatures (people). So had he been of sincere intention to Allah<sup>azwj</sup>, He<sup>azwj</sup> would Give him that which he wants in (a time period) quicker than that’."
        ]
      }
    }
